prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Calculate budget balance by summing advert costs, adding overheads percentage, and subtracting from planned budget.",
      "evidence_quote": "This is calculated by summing the cost of all the adverts in a campaign, adding a percentage for overheads and subtracting the result from the planned budget."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Display client list in Client dropdown when user selects a client.",
      "evidence_quote": "The Client dropdown displays a list of clients. When a client is selected, their campaigns will be displayed in the Campaign dropdown."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable Campaign dropdown with campaign list after client selection.",
      "evidence_quote": "When a client is selected, a list of campaigns is loaded into the Campaign dropdown."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable Check button when user selects a campaign.",
      "evidence_quote": "The Campaign dropdown displays a list of campaigns belonging to the client selected in the Client dropdown. When a campaign is selected the Check button is enabled."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Display budget calculation result in Budget textfield.",
      "evidence_quote": "The Budget textfield displays the result of the calculation to check the budget."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Perform budget balance calculation when user clicks Check button.",
      "evidence_quote": "The Check button causes the calculation of the budget balance to take place."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Clear Budget textfield when user selects a new client or campaign.",
      "evidence_quote": "It is cleared whenever a new client is selected or a new campaign is selected. It is not editable."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Disable Check button when user selects a new client.",
      "evidence_quote": "The Check button is disabled whenever a new client is selected."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Display alert dialogue with 'Close window? Are you sure?' message and OK/Cancel buttons when user clicks Close button.",
      "evidence_quote": "When the Close button is clicked, an alert dialogue is displayed. This asks ‘Close window? Are you sure?’ and displays two buttons labelled OK and Cancel."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Exit use case when user clicks OK in alert dialogue.",
      "evidence_quote": "If OK is clicked the window is exited; if Cancel is clicked then it carries on in the state it was in before the close button was clicked."
    }
  ]
}

